extrapolation to data fainter by one magnitude than the training
set. The photometric redshifts were derived with ANN and modeled
with Gaussian uncertainties. The test-data redshift error (mean
and scatter) equals 0.009 {\ensuremath{\pm}} 0.12 in the safe
subset and {\ensuremath{-}}0.0004 {\ensuremath{\pm}} 0.19 in the
extrapolation, averaged over a redshift range of 0.14 < z < 3.63
(first and 99th percentiles). Our success of the extrapolation
challenges the way that models are optimized and applied at the
faint data end. The resulting catalog is ready for cosmology and
active galactic nucleus (AGN) studies.
