sufficiently low and within our stringent requirements. With a
shear-ratio null-test, we verify the expected redshift scaling
of the galaxy-galaxy lensing signal around luminous red
galaxies. We conclude that the joint KiDS-1000 shear and
photometric redshift calibration is sufficiently robust for
combined-probe gravitational lensing and spectroscopic
clustering analyses.}},
