Sets of E/B-Integrals) analysis with complementary analyses of
the two-point shear correlation function and band power spectra,
finding the results to be in excellent agreement. We investigate
the sensitivity of all three statistics to a number of
measurement, astrophysical, and modelling systematics, finding
our S$_{8}$ constraints to be robust and dominated by
statistical errors. Our cosmological analysis of different
divisions of the data passes the Bayesian internal consistency
tests, with the exception of the second tomographic bin. As this
bin encompasses low-redshift galaxies, carrying insignificant
levels of cosmological information, we find that our results are
unchanged by the inclusion or exclusion of this sample.}},
