construct tests that can distinguish general relativity from its
potential modifications. We used the latest weak gravitational
lensing dataset from the Kilo-Degree Survey, KiDS-1000, in
conjunction with overlapping galaxy spectroscopic redshift
surveys, BOSS and 2dFLenS, to perform the most precise existing
amplitude-ratio test. We measured the associated E$_{G}$
statistic with 15 - 20\% errors in five {\ensuremath{\Delta}}z =
0.1 tomographic redshift bins in the range 0.2 < z < 0.7 on
