and redshift-dependence of these measurements are consistent
with the theoretical expectation of general relativity in a
Universe with matter density {\ensuremath{\Omega}}$_{m}$ = 0.27
{\ensuremath{\pm}} 0.04. We demonstrate that our results are
robust against different analysis choices, including schemes for
correcting the effects of source photometric redshift errors,
and we compare the performance of angular and projected galaxy-
galaxy lensing statistics.}},
