the galaxies. We measure the angular two-point correlation
function of the red galaxies in four redshift bins, and
constrain the large scale bias of our red-sequence sample
assuming a fixed $\Lambda$CDM cosmology. We find consistent
linear biases for two luminosity-threshold samples (dense and
luminous). We find that our constraints are well characterized
