 abstract = {{Exploiting the full statistical power of future cosmic shear surveys
will necessitate improvements to the accuracy with which the
gravitational lensing signal is measured. We present a framework
for calibrating shear with image simulations that demonstrates
the importance of including realistic correlations between
galaxy morphology, size, and more importantly, photometric
redshifts. This realism is essential to ensure that selection
and shape measurement biases can be calibrated accurately for a
tomographic cosmic shear analysis. We emulate Kilo-Degree Survey
