any issues. We measure a significant difference of the alignment
signal between the g, r and i-band observations. This difference
exceeds the amplitude of the linear alignment model on scales
below 2 Mpc h$^{-1}$. Separating the sample into
central/satellite and red/blue galaxies, we find that the
